Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_abstract_view(25.10)                            init_abstract_view(25.10)

Name
       init_abstract_view

Syntax
        init_abstract_view <list_of_views>

       Type: String

       Default: abstract

       Specifies  the  OpenAccess  view  names that the tool should examine to
       find the equivalent LEF MACRO information (for example, PINS, OBS, FOR-
       EIGN). If this value is null (""), the tool uses abstract as the value.
       The  init_abstract_view  variable   replaces   the   previous   rda_In-
       put(ui_oa_abstractname) configuration file variable.

       The  init_abstract_view is used in combination with init_oa_ref_lib and
       in the case where a Verilog netlist is read and views from the init_ab-
       stract_view list are used for on-demand loading for cells that were not
       processed from the libraries in the init_oa_ref_lib list. It is used by
       the init_design command.

Example
              * The following command sets ABS1 as the OpenAccess view  to  be
                examined for equivalent LEF MACRO information.

                set init_abstract_view {ABS1}

Related Information
              * init_design

              * init_oa_ref_lib

